<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11332&amp;p=129771#p129771</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11332&amp;p=129771#p129771"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: how can i change chr in PPU at runtime?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11332&amp;p=129771#p129771"><![CDATA[
1. Use RAM and write to the $0000 to $1FFF region in the PPU from the PRG-ROM data to put in new graphics.<br /><br />2. Use a mapper that banks CHR-ROM like MMC1 or MMC1 or something and swap in new banks of character. If you only have 1 to 4 sets of characters, option 2 should be fine. If your game is very dynamic, option 1 will be better over all, probably.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Tue Jun 10, 2014 9:30 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
